# lld --symbol-ordering-file
#
# Hot-startup symbol order for `bun <file>` / `bun run` / `bun --version`.
# lld clusters the symbols listed here at the front of `.text`, packing the
# init-array-reachable + CLI-dispatch + transpiler/VM bring-up code into one
# contiguous run of `.text` pages instead of letting it scatter across the
# ~50 MB `.text` blob (fat-LTO emits the ~14k Rust `.text.*` sections in
# arbitrary CGU / crate-alphabetical order, so hot bun_clap / bun_runtime
# code otherwise shares 64 KB fault-around windows with cold bun_install /
# bun_bundler / bun_css bodies).
#
# This is a single-pass, best-effort hint: lld silently ignores entries it
# can't resolve (paired with -Wl,--no-warn-symbol-ordering in flags.ts), so a
# slightly-stale list — Rust v0 mangling bakes in per-crate `Cs<hash>_`
# disambiguators and post-LTO `.llvm.<N>` suffixes that churn — just loses a
# little clustering and costs zero extra link time. Refresh when convenient:
#   perf record -e cycles:u -- ./build/release/bun trivial.js
#   perf script -F sym | awk 'NF{print $1}' | sort -u
# Linux release only (see flags.ts).
#
# Order: .init_array / libc / mimalloc init -> main -> Rust CLI entry ->
# arg parse -> run-command -> resolver/transpiler bring-up -> JSC VM init.

# .init_array targets + libc/cpu feature init
_start
frame_dummy
__cpu_indicator_init
register_tm_clones
_GLOBAL__sub_I_eh_alloc.cc
_GLOBAL__sub_I.00090_globals_io.cc
_GLOBAL__sub_I_cxx11_locale_inst.cc
_GLOBAL__sub_I_cxx11_wlocale_inst.cc
_GLOBAL__sub_I_locale_inst.cc
_GLOBAL__sub_I_system_error.cc
_GLOBAL__sub_I_ios_errcat.cc

# mimalloc fast path (touched before Rust main)
_ZL17mi_process_attachv
_ZL20mi_process_init_oncev
_ZL18mi_heap_init_theapPK9mi_heap_s
mi_thread_init
mi_malloc
mi_zalloc
mi_free

# entry — Rust CLI boot chain: main -> Cli::start -> Command::start
#   -> Command::which (argv->Tag) -> Command::create_context_data
#   (-> Arguments::parse, see the clap block below) -> dispatch.
# These are each `#[inline(never)]` at their definition site (see
# src/runtime/cli/mod.rs) precisely so they stay concrete symbols lld can
# anchor here instead of fat-LTO inlining-and-scattering them.
main
